leads.lead_text: Leaves less than 5 cm long; perianth to c. 7 mm long at maturity, limb usually less than half as long as tube; plants slender, few-branched, rarely 1 m high
Leaves 5–12 cm long; perianth 7–9 mm long at maturity, limb c. as long as tube; plants usually much-branched and more than 1 m high when flowering
Leaves spreading widely, arcuate, to c. 1.5 mm wide, rarely wider; common peduncles longer than branches of inflorescence; perianth usually white or bluish; far western Victoria only
Leaves erect or spreading, more or less straight, mostly 1.5–3 mm wide; common peduncles not significantly longer than branches of inflorescence; perianth white or cream; far eastern Victoria only
